'''Amidala's Beach''' was a private<ref name="SWG:LAPB" /> [[Beach/Legends|beach]] island located in [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo's]] [[Lake Country/Legends|Lake Country]],<ref name="SWG:AB">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=poi|Amidala's Beach|Naboo}}</ref> located in close proximity to [[Varykino/Legends|Varykino]], the ancestral home owned by [[Naberrie family/Legends|House Naberrie]].<ref name="AOTC" />

==History==
[[File:AmidalasPrivateBeachIsland.jpg|220px|thumb|The small island served as Amidala's private beach.]]
[[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]] stayed there with [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] before the start of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] when her life was being threatened by a [[Jango Fett/Legends|bounty hunter]], who was hired by [[Nute Gunray/Legends|Nute Gunray]] to [[Death/Legends|kill]] her. According to Padmé, when she was in [[Level Three]], she and her fellow classmates frequently swam to the island during school retreat,<ref name="AOTC" /> where an elderly jeweler crafted beautiful vases and [[Necklace/Legends|necklaces]] out of [[Glass/Legends|glass]].<ref name="AOTC novel">[[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones (novelization)|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'' novelization]]</ref> This was where Padmé had made plans to raise her child, although she died in childbirth, giving birth to [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke]] and [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Skywalker]].<ref name="ROTS">{{Film|III}}</ref>

In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> some spacers visited the location.<ref name="SWG:AB" />

==Behind the scenes==
Amidala's Beach was a location in the [[2003]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'', a [[Wikipedia:Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|massively multiplayer online roleplaying game]] developed by [[Sony]] Online Entertainment and published by [[LucasArts]],<ref name="SWG:AB" /> prior to its closure on [[December 15]], [[2011]].<ref name="Shutdown">{{SonyCite|url=playerinfo|text=IMPORTANT INFORMATION ABOUT ''STAR WARS'' GALAXIES™}}</ref> When the player visited the beach, they were awarded with an [[W:c:swg:Exploration badges|exploration badge]] for the area.<ref name="SWG:LAPB" />

